snippet.textDisplay: My thoughts are dancing around, twirling around, trying to mix in with you like creamer in black coffee. We talk it off well as strangers. This feeling is new to me and I’m terrified, but you made it comfortable in a strange way. Is it safe? You are sweet but these scars don’t trust easily, I take one step in and see someone I don’t know. It scares me knowing who you really are. Why are there two faces to this stranger? Which one is really you? Time with you makes me see colour where there was only grey. You are a different kind of cocktail, not my flavour but do I want vanilla? The more I know, the more I try to distance myself from you. Christmas is around the corner and I can’t help but feel guilty. I’m wandering around looking for answers on shop windows. We are only playing right? My heart is crying because she knows the mind with the dagger is right. You are a beautiful stranger; our worlds seem the same on the surface but the truth is we are like day and night. Oh how I wish this was the last fairytale I am writing.
